<title>EQTC:Recipes:Tinkering:Geerloks</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" leftmargin="0" topmargin="0">
Geerloks are wonderful little gadgets that give a 5 percent boost to your skill when performing combines. Note that they do <b>not</b> change the actual trivial ranking of an item, but do change your virtual skill when the game is computing success or failure.  It also boosts your virtual skill for skill-restricted combines, allowing you to attempt such combines at lower skill level than those without +skill modifiers.  For more details, see the article on geerloks and +skill items.<p>

These items are made by gnomes using their cultural tinkering skill. <b>Please note that while non-gnomes can perform these combines, they have only a slim chance of success, and they cannot receive skillups from the attempts.</b>
